      %p
        It is hard not to get excited when summer comes around.
        There is all that lovely warm weather to look forward to and the prospect of all that outdoor fun.
        Have you checked your summer wardrobe yet?
        Are you sure all your outfits will work perfectly for you whilst you are out enjoying all that lovely summer sun?
      %p
        Getting ready for summer often starts with having your wardrobe in perfect order in plenty of good time.
        So, if you haven’t got around to it yet, you might want to go and check in with your wardrobe and make sure your summer outfits are all good to go. 

      %p
        I believe that checking in with your wardrobe early is an essential pre-summer necessity, especially if you have a vacation or a staycation planned.
        Simply knowing you have everything you need now, will ensure you can spend more of your time enjoying the sun and less time worrying about what you are going to wear or what you might have forgotten.	
  
      %p
        Before you get ready to kick back, or jet off somewhere hot to relax, let’s talk about your key essentials for surviving the hot weather,
        like a summer hat.
        If you have never worn a summer hat before, then you might be the kind of person that always tries to skip them altogether.
        I recently discovered that the most popular reason to stop people from buying an essential item like the summer hat is not really knowing where to start.
        Generally, most people felt a little overwhelmed with too many options and questions and gave up before they even got started.
        Questions like "where do you start?" and "what do you look for?" caused the most confusion.
        With summer fast approaching it’s no wonder most people choose to skip buying a summer hat altogether.
        
