  .article-section.article-section-right-image.text-first.article-half-page-image-floated
    .article-text
      %h3
        Summer hats - find the perfect one

      .article-image.aspect-2-3
        -image_url = image_path("blog/summer-hat-for-style/sun-hat-yellow-jumpsuit.jpg")
        =image_tag(image_url, alt: "A woman wearing a stylish wide-brimmed summer hat, a yellow jumpsuit, and a white handbag with bold roses pattern.")
        %figcaption
          Photo by
          =link_to('Godisable Jacob', 'https://www.pexels.com/photo/woman-wearing-fascinator-hat-and-yellow-jumpsuit-1270014')
          on Pexels

      %p
        I strongly believe that there is a perfect hat out there for everyone.
        But before you begin to decide otherwise, let me ask you a quick question.
        Have you ever passed someone in a hat and immediately noticed how it suited them?
        Hats suit a lot of people but you have to pick the right one.
        It's the one that suits you, your wardrobe, and your personal taste all in one.
        Seeing someone walk by in a perfect hat is proof that it can work.
        With a little thought and a look at your current summer wardrobe, you can very easily find that perfect hat for you and your wardrobe too. 
        This is the magic of finding your perfect hat.

      %h4
        Your journey to finding your perfect hat starts here

      %p
        Taking the journey to choosing the right hat for you and your summer wardrobe is the key to obtaining that magic confidence you see in others,
        and if you do it right you will be wearing your hat all summer long with confidence.
        Fortunately, I have a really easy way to start.
        Follow these key steps and choosing a hat will become much easier.
        Firstly, it’s important to know what you currently have in your wardrobe and plan to wear with your summer hat.
        This will help you understand two key things: what will work for you and what will not. 

      %h2
        4 Hurdles to get over when choosing the right hat

      %p
        There are four key hurdles to get over when thinking about choosing the right hat for you: confidence, purpose, colour, and style.
        Let's start by looking at the first hurdle:
        
      %h3
        1. Confidence - if you aren’t confident in your hat then you won’t look it

      %p.strong
        Be more comfortable wearing a summer hat.

      %p
        Hats are generally worn throughout the year and for many reasons and occasions, so there are already lots to choose from. 
        
      %p
        You have probably already been to at least one special event where people were wearing hats.
        A wedding, a christening, and let's not forget the lovely races.
        It is usually considered an optional choice to wear a hat at any one of these events,
        but they are still the most popular places to see one or be seen wearing one.
        And let’s face it some are absolutely amazing.

      %p
        If you have ever attended one of these events did you notice at least one great hat?
        Do you remember how it first caught your eye?
        Did you notice the person wearing it too?
        Do you remember how confident they looked? How many times have you seen a hat on someone and thought they looked amazing and extremely confident?
        I have mentioned it once already, but this is the magic of wearing a well-styled hat and I think we can agree that we do think that people look great in hats.
        It’s uplifting, confidence building and ever so stylish, so there is no need to be afraid of them or of wearing one.
        Buying and choosing a hat for an event is much more personal than you think.
        Wearing only the right hat gives that all-day confidence you see in others and choosing a summer hat is no different.

      %p
        Let's move on to the next hurdle.

      %h3
        2. Purpose - Do you want style or protection or both?
      
      %p
        So, let’s start by asking the following important but very simple questions.
        Would you want style as your top priority for your hat, or are you looking for sun protection or maybe even both?
        If you are looking for sun protection then you might want to read my article on
        = succeed "," do
          =link_to('summer hats for protection', article_path(id='summer_hat_for_protection'))
        it details what is available and how to get the right kind of protection for you.
        But, if you are looking for style then there are lots of options to choose from.
        Firstly, we need to consider what you think you might feel most comfortable wearing.
        There is absolutely no point wearing a great big sombrero-style hat if you think you might feel like a bit of an idiot wearing it.
        This is why it’s so important to take the journey to finding your perfect hat and to take it one step at a time, especially if you want the final results to work for you.
        It’s a journey of your own personal taste and everyone is going to think differently along the way and everyone will choose a different hat by the end of it. 

      %p
        Let’s look at the third hurdle.

      %h3
        3. Colour - if don’t like the colour of your hat then you probably won’t wear it

      %p.strong
        How to choose the right colour summer hat for you?

      %p
        Let's start by taking a look at your wardrobe to help you find the perfect colour for your lovely summer hat.
        Your current wardrobe is a good place to start because then you can start to really understand your preferred hat style and colour.
        To get started try thinking about your favourite colours, and your own personal style.
        If you are not sure then it is a good idea to take a good look at just your summer wardrobe.
        This is because these are items you have already chosen to own and wear this summer.
        Try picking out your perfect colour combinations from what you see before you, in your wardrobe.
        If you can’t see anything standing out then try taking some favourite items out and laying them on your bed for a better look.
        Pick out a few key colours that stand out to you, that you know you love and wear often.
        You want to be looking for the main colours you like in your general style and across all your outfits.
        Ask yourself what colour you think you wear the most. If nothing stands out then you can try looking for secondary colours too.
        These are colours that are present in more than a few of your items but not in a bold way, in more of a subtle way.
        These secondary colours are a great option to get you started too.
        
      %p
        If you are still struggling, I have created a quick 4-step process to help you further.
        
      %p
        These are 4 main questions and 4 secondary questions to think about.
        You are looking to identify both your key colour and main style at the end:

