      %p.strong
        What style of hat do you like?

      %p
        A few weeks ago, I spent a little time sitting and drinking tea outside while observing people at a popular tourist attraction.
        It was a lovely sunny day and I noticed quite a few people wearing really great hats.
        Did you know just how many great hat styles exist?
        Did you know how many there are to choose from?
        I saw quite a few variations of the straw hats alone.
        I found these were 8 top styles being worn on that day.
        Some were on trend for the current season and some were classics that never go out of style.
        If you are not sure what style to look for just yet, I have provided some helpful short descriptions for each of the styles I saw and how their look was generally being worn.
        This should help you pinpoint a style and look that appeals to you the most and it should help get you started on your path to finding your one true summer hat.

      %p
        The main hats I saw on display were the Fedora, the Bucket hat, a Baseball cap, the Boater, the Panama hat, the Cowboy hat, and the Boonie.

